Kirinyaga governor ann Waiguru is now accusing the deputy President William ruto of supervising jubilee members of parliament to disrespect President Uhuru Kenyatta. Speaking at Kagio market while launching garbage skips, the governor said that members of parliament from the mt Kenya region who have been insulting and disrespecting the president have been doing so with the blessings of the deputy president. Waiguru argues that there is no time the deputy president has condemned the MPs for disrespecting the president even though they do so at his meetings.